selectInst(25.10)                                            selectInst(25.10)

Name
       selectInst  -  Selects an instance and highlights it in the design dis-
       play window

Syntax
       selectInst

       [-help]

       <instName> | {<list_of_instNames>}

       Selects an instance and highlights it in the design display window. You
       can use this command after importing or restoring the design.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each selectInst parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man selectInst

       <instName>
              Specifies  the  name  of one or more than one insts. You can use
              wildcards (*) to specify inst names.

              Data_type: (inst)+, required

Example:
              * The following command selects nets and highlights them in  the
                design display window:

                selectInst {reg1 reg2}

Related Information
              * queryFPlanObject

              * deselectInst

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

